<dc:title>CORE Jazz Album</dc:title>
<dc:subject>compilation jazz album CORE used as a fundraiser for the organization.</dc:subject>
<dc:description>RECORD ONE, SIDE ONE:    
Dinah Washington, &quot;The Blues Ain&#039;t Nothing But a Woman Cryin For Her Man&quot;; Cannonball Adderly with Machito and his Orchestra, &quot;Cannonology&quot;; Harry Belafante with Machito and his Orchestra, &quot;Lean on Me&quot;; Herbie Mann with Machito and his Orchestra, &quot;Carabunta&quot;; Steve Allen&#039;s Roundtable All-Stars, &quot;I Thought About You&quot;; Chris Connor and Maynard Ferguson, &quot;I Feel a Song Coming On&quot;.

RECORD ONE, SIDE TWO:
Louis Armstrong and Duke Ellington, &quot;Cotton Tail&quot;; John Coltrane Quartet, &quot;Exotica&quot;; Dizzy Gillespie, &quot;Paris Swing&quot;; Erroll Garner, &quot;Love for Sale&quot;; Woody Herman Sextet with Nat Adderley, &quot;Lullaby of Birdland&quot;; Charlie Parker &amp; Miles Davis, &quot;Klactoveededstene&quot;

RECORD TWO, SIDE ONE:
Stan Getz &amp; Horace Silver, &quot;Strike Up the Band&quot;; Art Tatum, &quot;Dark Eyes&quot;; Dizzy Gillespie &amp; Charlie Parker, &quot; Groovin&#039; High&quot;; J. J. Johnson &amp; Kai Winding, &quot;The Shrike&quot;; Bud Powell, &quot;Off Minor&quot;; Joe Newman &amp; Zoot Sims, &quot;Tater Pie&quot;

RECORD TWO, SIDE TWO:
Joe Williams With Count Basie &amp; His Orchestra, &quot;Everyday&quot;; Sarah Vaughan with Count Basie &amp; His Orchestra, &quot;Until I Met You&quot;; Count Basie &amp; His Orchestra, &quot;Tickle Toe&quot;; Joe Williams with Lambert, Hendricks &amp; Ross with Count Basie &amp; His Orchestra, &quot;Going to Chicago Blues&quot;; Billy Eckstine with Count Basie &amp; his Orchestra, &quot;Jelly, Jelly&quot;; Tony Bennett with count Basie &amp; his Orchestra, &quot;I Guess I&#039;ll Have to Change My Plans&quot;
</dc:description>
<dc:creator>A1, S1:  J. Mayo Williams, A. K. Salim, Green-Waldman, Herbie Mann, Van Heusen-Mercer, Oppenheim-McHugh-Fields

A1, S2: Duke Ellington; John Coltrane; Dizzy Gillespie; Cole Porter; Shearing-Foster, Charlie Parker

